JSP : Java Server Page
Advantages:
 i)Extension to the servlet
 ii)Easy to maintain
 iii)Fast development: No need to recompile and redeploy
 iv)Less code than servlet
 
 
 JSP Lifecycle:
 
 i)Tanslation of JSP page
 ii)Compilation of JSP page
 iii)Classloading
 iv)Instantiation(Object creation)
 v)Initialization(container invokes jspinit())
 vi)Request Processing(container invokes _jspService())
 vii)Destroy(container invokes jspDestroy())
 
 Container : Server
 
 Jsp : @ Directive
 
 Tags:
 i)Scriplet Tag   <%  code %>
 ii)Expression Tag <%= code %> 
 iii)Declaration Tag <%! code %>
 
 
 Implicit Object:
 i)Request
 ii)Response
 iii)Config
 iv)Application
 v)Session
 vi)PageContext
    Scopes: page, request, session, application
 vii)Page(Object)
 viii)Exception
 
 Error Page: 404
 
 
 
 Directives:
 i)Page  : <%@ page attribute="value" %>
 ii)Include
 iii)Taglib
 
 Web Application: Multiple page
 
 
 
 